<body>
<p>All of us in <italic>LUPUS</italic> were saddened to hear of the death of Duncan Gordon. Duncan, who took over the editorship of the <italic>Journal of Rheumatology</italic> from its founder Metro Orgryzlo, and gave unwavering commitment to the task he inherited.</p>
<p>Under Duncan’s quiet and friendly leadership, ‘<italic>J Rheumatol</italic>’ was steered to pre-eminence in the world of rheumatology – becoming arguably the world’s leading clinically oriented rheumatology journal.</p>
<p>I personally will greatly miss his down to earth friendship.</p>
